      "message": "that\u0027s okay by me; i think that something like this is equivalent: `^[\\w@%+:,./-][\\w@%+\u003d:,./-]*$`\n\ni had to look at https://github.com/google/re2/wiki/Syntax to remind myself of exactly what \\w matches ([0-9A-Za-z_]), so you may want to document that in the comment here too. :-)\n\nor something like this may be clearer:\n\n const (\n     // Leading equals sign is unsafe ...\n     leadingSafeChars \u003d `-\\w@%+:,./`\n     trailingSafeChars \u003d leadingSafeChars + \"\u003d\"\n )\n \n // safeRE matches ...\n var safeRE \u003d regexp.MustCompile(fmt.Sprintf(\"^[%s][%s]*$\", leadingSafeChars, trailingSafeChars))",
